
@startuml

' Define classes and their attributes

class Bank {
  +String name
}

class Branch {
  +String branchName
  +String location
}

class Customer {
  +String firstName
  +String lastName
}

class Account {
  +int accountNumber
  +double balance
}

class CurrentAccount {
  +double overdraftLimit
}

class SavingsAccount {}

' Define associations and relationships

Bank "1" *-- "many" Branch : contains
Bank "1" *-- "many" Customer : manages
Customer "1" --> "1..5" Account : has
Account "1" ^-- "1" CurrentAccount : extends
Account "1" ^-- "1" SavingsAccount : extends

@enduml

### Explanation of the Diagram:

- **`Bank`**:
  - Manages multiple `Customer`s.
  - Has multiple `Branch`es.

- **`Customer`**:
  - Has between 1 and 5 `Account`s.
  - Each customer has a first and last name.

- **`Account`**:
  - Abstract base class with common properties: `accountNumber`, `balance`.
  - Extended by `CurrentAccount` and `SavingsAccount`.

- **`CurrentAccount`**:
  - Has an additional attribute: `overdraftLimit`.

- **`SavingsAccount`**:
  - No extra attributes beyond those in `Account`.

